              "rel": "",
              "start": 130,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 201,
              "href": "http://www.debtdeflation.com/blogs/manifesto/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 197,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "665afc41aec4_37",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f0ae",
          "text": "A Basic Income. Scott Santens has been doing excellent work here.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 64,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@2noame",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 60,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "665afc41aec4_38",
          "href": null,
          "name": "92e1",
          "text": "The current stranglehold of elite influence on political power (in all of its many aspects) must be completely broken. Sovereignty must be returned to the people and new institutional forms must be developed that deliver on the necessities of governance at all levels while being intrinsically resilient to various forms of capture and corruption.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 117,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "665afc41aec4_39",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4dfa",
          "text": "Huge work is being done here and implementations of various flavors of “liquid democracy” and “eDemocracy” are playing a big part in the rise of new political parties in Europe.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 88,
              "href": "https://medium.com/@DomSchiener/liquid-democracy-true-democracy-for-the-21st-century-7c66f5e53b6f#.3w8dw2p99",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 72,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 105,
              "href": "http://www.citizens.is/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 95,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 166,
              "href": "http://grapevine.is/mag/articles/2015/04/15/how-the-pirates-are-taking-over-icelandic-politics/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 145,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "665afc41aec4_40",
          "href": null,
          "name": "a84f",
          "text": "Going farther, the people at places like BitNation are actively going beyond new forms of governance to prototype new forms of sovereignty. After all, the real life of the digital age is not bounded by geography. Why should governance be?",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 50,
              "href": "https://bitnation.co/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 41,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "665afc41aec4_41",
          "href": null,
          "name": "fd4b",
          "text": "All mechanisms of bad faith discourse, be they commercial, political or intellectual, must be rendered ineffective and their practitioners made to bear costs that make resorting to bad faith discourse irrational. New forms of information sharing, deliberation and truth seeking must be implemented that intrinsically reward good faith participation and extinguish bad faith defection.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 211,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "665afc41aec4_42",
          "href": null,
          "name": "f46d",
          "text": "As our information environment overwhelms legacy channels like Television and Newspapers, new approaches to the attention and reputation economy are beginning to “select-against” bad faith discourse and upregulate only that which is actually helpful and useful.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 73,
              "href": "http://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2014/02/tv-is-dead-now-what-103670",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 31,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 121,
              "href": "http://www.synereo.com/learn-more/",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 112,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 136,
              "href": "https://www.ted.com/talks/rachel_botsman_the_currency_of_the_new_economy_is_trust?language=en#t-70454",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 126,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 260,
              "href": "https://medium.com/emergent-culture/the-wellbeing-economy-89c67b625ac2#.gp23w8db2",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 242,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "ULI"
        },
        {
          "id": "665afc41aec4_43",
          "href": null,
          "name": "8ae2",
          "text": "Finally, Forgiveness. One of the many consequences of our old social operating system and in particular its perversion and capture by the oligarchy has been a vast injustice on a global scale. There is no way to resolve this injustice, no way to balance the scales or provide revenge or retribution. There is no path forward but forgiveness. For those who commit to the Jubilee, there must be a commitment similar to the Truth and Reconciliation efforts in Argentina and South Africa. So long as the fundamental structure of the new system is likely to be just. So long as the new world is likely to deliver systemic justice, we accept that past injustice is in the past.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 20,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 9,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "STRONG",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
